Sentencas: Stresses and probability of failure during operation of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is affected by the deformational properties of the different components of the SOFC stack.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: Though the overall stress relaxes with time during steady state operation, large stresses would normally appear through transients in operation including temporary shut downs.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: These stresses are highly affected by the transient creep behavior of metallic components in the SOFC stack.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: This study investigates whether a variation of the so-called Chaboche's unified power law together with isotropic hardening can represent the transient behavior of Crofer 22 APU, a typical iron-chromium alloy used in SOFC stacks.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: The material parameters for the model are determined by measurements involving relaxation and constant strain rate experiments.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: The constitutive law is implemented into commercial finite element software using a user defined material model.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: This is used to validate the developed constitutive law to experiments with constant strain rate, cyclic and creep experiments.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: The predictions from the developed model are found to agree well with experimental data.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: It is therefore concluded that Chaboche's unified power law can be applied to describe the high temperature inelastic deformational behaviors of Crofer 22 APU used for metallic interconnects in SOFC stacks.
Titulo: Transient deformational properties of high temperature alloys used in solid oxide fuel cell stacks
